main event: Two objects were observed in the northern sky moving in different patterns for a duration of 90 minutes.
interesting points: The objects exhibited varying brightness during their movement, becoming dim and almost invisible at certain angles., Both objects were observed simultaneously using binoculars at one point., The conclusion indicates that the observed objects were likely aircraft, although there was no definitive evidence of this., Observers noted one object passed into the field of view of the binoculars while tracking the other., The sighting took place under bright conditions with no clouds in the sky.
sighted object: two unidentified objects in the sky
witness description: Two individuals, one of whom has a B.S. and M.S. in Physics.
